TITLE: Defining Custom Property Type in A-Frame Component Schema
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a custom property type with parse and stringify functions for handling slash-delimited strings as arrays in an A-Frame component schema.
SOURCE: https://github.com/aframevr/aframe/blob/master/docs/core/component.md#2025-04-23_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
schema: {
  // Parse slash-delimited string to an array (e.g., `foo="myProperty: a/b"` to `['a', 'b']`),
  // stringify array to string (e.g., `['a', 'b']` to `foo="myProperty: a/b"`)
  myProperty: {
    default: [],
    parse: function (value) {
      return value.split('/');
    },
    stringify: function (value) {
      return value.join('/');
    }
  }
}
```

